# Compiled ACLiC/ROOT build products -- these are platform-specific (the ones
# currently on disk here are macOS/arm64 Mach-O binaries) and must be rebuilt
# fresh on whatever machine actually runs them (in particular: rebuilt on an
# SDCC/RCF Linux node before submitting any batch job, per the "SDCC batch
# submission" README section -- a macOS-built .so will not load on BNL's Linux
# nodes). Only source is tracked; every clone (laptop or SDCC) runs its own
# one-time build per the README's "One-time build setup" section.
bin/*.so
bin/*.d
bin/*.pcm
submodule/PicoDstReader_SL24y/*.o
submodule/PicoDstReader_SL24y/libStPicoDst.so
submodule/PicoDstReader_SL24y/*_rdict.pcm
submodule/PicoDstReader_SL24y/StPicoDst_Dict.C
*.d

# Old SL23a-vendored PicoDst reader submodule, replaced 2026-07-02 by
# PicoDstReader_SL24y (see README's "PicoDst reader version" section). This directory
# is no longer tracked -- excluded entirely (not just its build artifacts) rather than
# leaving stale source alongside the new submodule. If this directory still physically
# exists in your checkout, it's safe to delete it (`rm -rf submodule/PicoDstReader_SL23a`).
submodule/PicoDstReader_SL23a/

# ROOT ACLiC intermediate artifacts that can show up alongside sources
*_ACLiC_dict_rdict.pcm
*.pcm.d

# Local run outputs / scratch (yield files, spectra files, fit outputs, plots) --
# these are analysis outputs, not code, and are typically large. Re-derive them by
# re-running the pipeline rather than committing them.
*.root
!submodule/ParticleInfo/PidFunctions_Data/*.root
spectra_plots/
spectrafit_images/

# OS cruft
.DS_Store

# Ad-hoc scratch/backup copies made while iterating on a macro or source file (manual
# "before I edit this, save a copy" snapshots, e.g. _to_delete_recheck_*.C,
# _to_delete_rev5base_*.C) -- never meant to be committed, just kept around long enough
# to diff against. Ignore both the loose files (in case one gets created directly in
# place again) and the _to_delete/ holding folder they get swept into before manual
# deletion.
_to_delete_*
_to_delete/
